RESOLUTION.DESC:
The Security Council,

Ever vigilant in its oversight of the multiverse and the conduct of nations within it,

Observes with profound concern that [region]Hawaiian Isle[/region], operating under the influence and manipulation of [nation]Obvious Puppet 1[/nation], has transformed what should be governance into a vast exercise in neglect, bureaucracy, and administrative obsession.

Noting that [region]Hawaiian Isle[/region] oversees 220 subordinate nations yet leaves the vast majority of their political and social fates abandoned, creating over 200 billion citizens who exist not as autonomous actors but as instruments of governance, their lives reduced to tools of convenience no better than a stroke of a pen;

[b]Alarmed by the obsessive surveillance, restrictions, and micromanagement of [region]Hawaiian Isle[/region]:[/b]
[list]
[i]1. Citizens are monitored from childhood[/i], their conversations scanned for signs of radicalization, and their freedoms limited to voting, participation in trivialized bureaucratic processes, and receipt of mandatory wood distributions from Leader;
[i]2. Economic and cultural activity is strictly controlled[/i], dominated by state-managed Furniture Restoration, basket weaving, Information Technology, and Retail, while any genuine opportunity for creativity, self-determination, or advancement is largely denied;
[i]3. Public records and statistical absurdities[/i], such as trout fishing sector rankings, census inaccuracies explained with &#147;Sith happens,&#148; and Ventriloquism as the national religion, demonstrate a government preoccupied with minutiae rather than meaningful governance;
[i]4. Regional diplomacy is obstructed[/i] by bans and embassy rejections, leaving neighboring nations unable to engage meaningfully and creating a bureaucratic purgatory for all under [region]Hawaiian Isle[/region]&#146;s influence.
[/list]

Recognizing that these failures are not solely the result of [region]Hawaiian Isle[/region] itself, but stem from the direction and control of [nation]Obvious Puppet 1[/nation], whose obsessive micromanagement ensures that the puppet state enforces power at the expense of life, liberty, and meaningful agency;

[b]Strongly condemns [region]Hawaiian Isle[/region][/b] for enabling and perpetuating one of the gravest acts against the multiverse: the creation of billions of citizens as depersonalized tools, the abdication of true governance, and the reduction of entire nations to instruments of administrative convenience;

Urges [region]Hawaiian Isle[/region], under the oversight of [nation]Obvious Puppet 1[/nation], to restore autonomy to its constituent nations, respect the agency of all citizens, and recognize that governance carries moral responsibilities beyond mere control, bans, and spreadsheets;

The Security Council, affirming that no nation should wield power over billions of lives only to reduce them to instruments of its own obsession,

[b]Hereby Condemns [region]Hawaiian Isle[/region].[/b]
